I'll create a Java application using gRPC for a library management system. Here are the necessary files:

First, let's define the Protocol Buffers service specification:

```proto:library.proto
syntax = "proto3";

option java_multiple_files = true;
option java_package = "com.example.library";
option java_outer_classname = "LibraryProto";

package library;

// Library Service definition
service LibraryService {
  // Adds a new book to the library
  rpc AddBook (AddBookRequest) returns (AddBookResponse) {}

  // Retrieves book details by ID
  rpc GetBook (GetBookRequest) returns (GetBookResponse) {}

  // Deletes a book by ID
  rpc DeleteBook (DeleteBookRequest) returns (DeleteBookResponse) {}
}

// Book message represents a book in the library
message Book {
  string id = 1;
  string title = 2;
  string author = 3;
  int32 year = 4;
}

// Request to add a new book
message AddBookRequest {
  Book book = 1;
}

// Response after adding a book
message AddBookResponse {
  bool success = 1;
  string message = 2;
  Book book = 3;
}

// Request to get a book by ID
message GetBookRequest {
  string book_id = 1;
}

// Response for get book request
message GetBookResponse {
  bool success = 1;
  string message = 2;
  Book book = 3;
}

// Request to delete a book by ID
message DeleteBookRequest {
  string book_id = 1;
}

// Response after deleting a book
message DeleteBookResponse {
  bool success = 1;
  string message = 2;
}
```

Now, let's implement the server:

```java:LibraryServer.java
package com.example.library;

import io.grpc.Server;
import io.grpc.ServerBuilder;

import java.io.IOException;

public class LibraryServer {
    private Server server;
    private final int port = 50051;

    public void start() throws IOException {
        server = ServerBuilder.forPort(port)
                .addService(new LibraryServiceImpl())
                .build()
                .start();

        System.out.println("Server started, listening on port " + port);

        Runtime.getRuntime().addShutdownHook(new Thread(() -> {
            System.out.println("Shutting down gRPC server");
            LibraryServer.this.stop();
            System.out.println("Server shut down");
        }));
    }

    private void stop() {
        if (server != null) {
            server.shutdown();
        }
    }

    public void blockUntilShutdown() throws InterruptedException {
        if (server != null) {
            server.awaitTermination();
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException, InterruptedException {
        final LibraryServer server = new LibraryServer();
        server.start();
        server.blockUntilShutdown();
    }
}
```

Next, the service implementation:

```java:LibraryServiceImpl.java
package com.example.library;

import io.grpc.Status;
import io.grpc.stub.StreamObserver;

import java.util.HashMap;
import java.util.Map;
import java.util.UUID;

public class LibraryServiceImpl extends LibraryServiceGrpc.LibraryServiceImplBase {

    // In-memory database for storing books
    private final Map<String, Book> books = new HashMap<>();

    @Override
    public void addBook(AddBookRequest request, StreamObserver<AddBookResponse> responseObserver) {
        Book book = request.getBook();

        // Generate a new ID if none provided
        if (book.getId().isEmpty()) {
            book = book.toBuilder().setId(UUID.randomUUID().toString()).build();
        }

        // Store the book
        books.put(book.getId(), book);

        // Build success response
        AddBookResponse response = AddBookResponse.newBuilder()
                .setSuccess(true)
                .setMessage("Book added successfully")
                .setBook(book)
                .build();

        responseObserver.onNext(response);
        responseObserver.onCompleted();
    }

    @Override
    public void getBook(GetBookRequest request, StreamObserver<GetBookResponse> responseObserver) {
        String bookId = request.getBookId();

        if (bookId.isEmpty()) {
            // Handle invalid ID
            responseObserver.onError(
                Status.INVALID_ARGUMENT
                    .withDescription("Book ID cannot be empty")
                    .asRuntimeException()
            );
            return;
        }

        if (books.containsKey(bookId)) {
            // Book found
            Book book = books.get(bookId);
            GetBookResponse response = GetBookResponse.newBuilder()
                    .setSuccess(true)
                    .setMessage("Book retrieved successfully")
                    .setBook(book)
                    .build();
            responseObserver.onNext(response);
            responseObserver.onCompleted();
        } else {
            // Book not found
            GetBookResponse response = GetBookResponse.newBuilder()
                    .setSuccess(false)
                    .setMessage("Book not found with ID: " + bookId)
                    .build();
            responseObserver.onNext(response);
            responseObserver.onCompleted();
        }
    }

    @Override
    public void deleteBook(DeleteBookRequest request, StreamObserver<DeleteBookResponse> responseObserver) {
        String bookId = request.getBookId();

        if (bookId.isEmpty()) {
            // Handle invalid ID
            responseObserver.onError(
                Status.INVALID_ARGUMENT
                    .withDescription("Book ID cannot be empty")
                    .asRuntimeException()
            );
            return;
        }

        if (books.containsKey(bookId)) {
            // Remove book if exists
            books.remove(bookId);
            DeleteBookResponse response = DeleteBookResponse.newBuilder()
                    .setSuccess(true)
                    .setMessage("Book deleted successfully")
                    .build();
            responseObserver.onNext(response);
            responseObserver.onCompleted();
        } else {
            // Book not found
            DeleteBookResponse response = DeleteBookResponse.newBuilder()
                    .setSuccess(false)
                    .setMessage("Cannot delete: Book not found with ID: " + bookId)
                    .build();
            responseObserver.onNext(response);
            responseObserver.onCompleted();
        }
    }
}
```

Finally, let's create a client to test the service:

```java:LibraryClient.java
package com.example.library;

import io.grpc.ManagedChannel;
import io.grpc.ManagedChannelBuilder;
import io.grpc.StatusRuntimeException;

import java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;
import java.util.logging.Level;
import java.util.logging.Logger;

public class LibraryClient {
    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(LibraryClient.class.getName());

    private final LibraryServiceGrpc.LibraryServiceBlockingStub blockingStub;
    private final ManagedChannel channel;

    public LibraryClient(String host, int port) {
        channel = ManagedChannelBuilder.forAddress(host, port)
                .usePlaintext()
                .build();
        blockingStub = LibraryServiceGrpc.newBlockingStub(channel);
    }

    public void shutdown() throws InterruptedException {
        channel.shutdown().awaitTermination(5, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
    }

    public void addBook(String title, String author, int year) {
        Book book = Book.newBuilder()
                .setTitle(title)
                .setAuthor(author)
                .setYear(year)
                .build();

        AddBookRequest request = AddBookRequest.newBuilder()
                .setBook(book)
                .build();

        try {
            AddBookResponse response = blockingStub.addBook(request);
            if (response.getSuccess()) {
                logger.info("Book added: " + response.getBook().getId());
            } else {
                logger.warning("Failed to add book: " + response.getMessage());
            }
        } catch (StatusRuntimeException e) {
            logger.log(Level.WARNING, "RPC failed: {0}", e.getStatus());
        }
    }

    public void getBook(String bookId) {
        GetBookRequest request = GetBookRequest.newBuilder()
                .setBookId(bookId)
                .build();

        try {
            GetBookResponse response = blockingStub.getBook(request);
            if (response.getSuccess()) {
                Book book = response.getBook();
                logger.info("Book found: ID=" + book.getId() + 
                           ", Title=" + book.getTitle() +
                           ", Author=" + book.getAuthor() +
                           ", Year=" + book.getYear());
            } else {
                logger.warning("Book not found: " + response.getMessage());
            }
        } catch (StatusRuntimeException e) {
            logger.log(Level.WARNING, "RPC failed: {0}", e.getStatus());
        }
    }

    public void deleteBook(String bookId) {
        DeleteBookRequest request = DeleteBookRequest.newBuilder()
                .setBookId(bookId)
                .build();

        try {
            DeleteBookResponse response = blockingStub.deleteBook(request);
            if (response.getSuccess()) {
                logger.info("Book deleted: " + response.getMessage());
            } else {
                logger.warning("Failed to delete book: " + response.getMessage());
            }
        } catch (StatusRuntimeException e) {
            logger.log(Level.WARNING, "RPC failed: {0}", e.getStatus());
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) throws InterruptedException {
        LibraryClient client = new LibraryClient("localhost", 50051);
        try {
            // Add a book
            client.addBook("The Great Gatsby", "F. Scott Fitzgerald", 1925);

            // Get the book (would need the actual ID from server response)
            String bookId = "some-book-id"; // In a real scenario, you'd use the ID from the add response
            client.getBook(bookId);

            // Delete the book
            client.deleteBook(bookId);

            // Try to get a non-existent book
            client.getBook("non-existent-id");
        } finally {
            client.shutdown();
        }
    }
}
```

For this application to work, you would need to include gRPC dependencies in your build file (such as Maven's pom.xml or Gradle's build.gradle) and generate the gRPC client and server classes from the Protocol Buffer definition.

